@@ -10,4 +10,9 @@ Exit protocol: write the ledger entry (decisions, splits with the
 <client>-<workflow>-<skill> naming, assumptions tagged to Information Requests,
 conventions), get my approval on it, then create/update the workflow's proposal
 from proposals/TEMPLATE.md including the skills list in frontmatter
-(shared deps first) and set status: proposed.
+(shared deps first) and set status: proposed. Then write the executable test
+suite for every skill in the proposal — skills/<skill>/eval/eval.yaml plus the
+fixture files it references — per grill-protocol rule 6. The builder must not
+author its own exam; fixtures you cannot produce become Information Request
+items in the Blockers table, but eval.yaml itself must exist or the conductor
+will block the proposal instead of building it.
